Package jsl.modeling.elements.queue

Interface Summary
QObjectSelectionRuleIfc  
QueueListenerIfc This interface should be implemented by classes that need to be notified when an object gets enqueued or when the object gets removed (via removeNext()) on a queue
 

Class Summary
FIFODiscipline The FIFODiscipline provides a mechanism to the Queue object for ordering the elements according to the first in, first out rule.
LIFODiscipline The LIFODiscipline provides a mechanism to the Queue object for ordering the elements according to the first in, first out rule.
QObject QObject can be used as a base class for objects that need to be placed in queues on a regular basis.
Queue The Queue class provides the ability to hold entities (QObjects) within the model.
QueueDiscipline The QueueDiscipline provides a mechanism to the Queue object for ordering the elements.
RandomDiscipline The RandomDiscipline provides a mechanism to the Queue object to provide a random selection of objects from the queue rule.
RankedQDiscipline The RankedQDiscipline provides a mechanism to the Queue object for ordering the elements according to a priority rule.
 

Enum Summary
Queue.Status ENQUEUED indicates that something was just enqueued DEQUEUED indicates that something was just dequeued
